    <div type="translation">
 	<!--translation encoded as per EG §9.2 -->
	<p>Om. Let there be no obstacle! As follows is the decree of Rahyaṅ Niskala Vastu Kañcana<!-- Aditia: we need to choose whether in translating we adapt spelling of names to EYD, or to "loose transliteration" as per TG. In the latter case, we would have here Rahyaṅ Niskala Vasti Kañcana. --><!-- Arlo: Maybe it is better to adapt our loose transliteration system here, since the translation is in english. -->, that came down to Rahyaṅ Niṅrat Kañcana<!-- Or: "the lord of Rat Kancana"? --> and also to His Highness now at Pakuan Pajajaran.</p> 
	<p>Do not omit to take care of the inhabitants of Jayagiri and the inhabitants of Sundasembawa.</p> 
	<p>If there is someone providing them livelihood, do not be eager to overcrowd them with the <foreign>dasa</foreign>, <foreign>calagara</foreign>, cotton <foreign>timbang</foreign>, rice paddies <foreign>dongdang</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation">taxes</supplied>.</p><!-- Aditia: some of the fiscal terms can actually be translated... --> <!-- Arlo: dasa and calagara are difficult to translate litterary, should we have a comment in xml file under commentary here? Or we should leave it like this and make some note in our draft?--> 
	<p>Also with regard to all the <supplied reason="subaudible">people at the</supplied> mouth of the river: do not be eager to ask them toll. Because those who are loved, as it were, <supplied reason="subaudible">themselves</supplied> love the world, <supplied reason="subaudible">and are those</supplied> who firmly put into practice the divine ordinances.</p> 
         </div>
